aWLICashValue_MixedProduct.Description: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss\fprq2\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}{\f1\fnil MS Sans Serif;}{\f2\fnil\fcharset2 Symbol;}} {\colortbl ;\red128\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang2057\f0\fs16 This allows you to convert a lump sum of money into an \cf1\b annuity\b0 \cf0 so that you can immediately \par receive income. Payments generally start about a month after you purchase the annuity. This \par type of annuity offers financial security in the form of income payments for the rest of your life. \par In other words, you cannot outlive it.\par \par \cf1\b Immediate annuities\cf0 \b0 allow you to:\par \pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720 Supplement your current income. If you are nearing retirement, you may consider \line transferring another savings or investment account into an immediate annuity. You \line can also move the proceeds from a deferred annuity into an immediate annuity.\par {\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Pay taxes only on the portion of your immediate annuity payments that is considered \line earnings. You are not taxed on the portion that is principal. The principal is the initial \line deposit made with funds that have already been taxed.\par \pard\par Like deferred annuities, immediate annuities can be fixed or variable. Fixed immediate annuity \par income payments are pegged to the amount you contribute, your age and the interest rate at \par the time of purchase. Those payments to you will not go up or down. \cf1\b Variable immediate \par annuity\b0 \cf0 payments vary with the investments you chose.\cf2\lang1036\f1\par }
